# Project Title (Working)

**Node-Based Visual Programming & Analysis Editor for Low-Level Programming**

(You can later rename it to something cooler: *HexFlow*, *AsmGraph*, *NodeASM*, etc.)

---

# 1. PLANNING & FEASIBILITY (SDLC Phase 1)

## Objective

Create a **node-based editor** that visually represents **assembly-level logic**, helps users:

* Write low-level programs visually
* Understand registers, memory, jumps
* Generate assembly code
* Analyze performance & errors

This tool helps **students, reverse engineers, and low-level developers**.

---

## Feasibility Analysis

### Technical Feasibility

‚úÖ Achievable using:

* **Frontend**: React + React Flow / custom canvas
* **Backend**: Spring Boot
* **DB**: PostgreSQL / MySQL
* **Real-time**: WebSockets
* **Parser**: Assembly parser module

### Economic Feasibility

* Open-source tools only
* No paid APIs required

### Operational Feasibility

* Students can use it in browser
* Lecturers can demonstrate visually

---

## Stakeholders

* Students
* Lecturers
* Low-level developers
* System admins

